Learn About Litigation Finance



Click Here to Download our Brochure


Litigation Finance
We provide funding to plaintiffs and their law firms engaged in large disputes, both in the U.S. and abroad. Our highly-experienced team dives into a case, assessing its merits, providing strategic guidance where desired, lining up experts to strengthen it, and — most importantly — deploy the funding needed to carry the case through to its best outcome. We share risk — we are repaid only if the case is successful — and we promote collaboration among client, law firm and funder. Click here for our Litigation Finance Form to send us information about your situation.



Litigation Finance - Expertise
• Complex business and commercial disputes 
                            • Intellectual property claims involving copyright, trademark and patent infringement 
                            • Product Liability and Tort Claims 
                            • Personal Injury 
                            • Medical Malpractice 
                            • Breach of contract 
                            • Breach of fiduciary duty 
                            • Bankruptcy and insolvency claims 
                            • Domestic and international arbitrations 
                            • Appeals 
                            • Whistleblower claims 
                            • Antitrust 
                            • Environmental 



Joint Venture Financing
TownCenter Partners LLC is actively pursuing real estate development and investment opportunities with experienced, well-capitalized partners. We will entertain joint venture development structures with land owners, developers, real estate operating companies, retailers, hospitals, doctor groups and other value-added service providers. We will also consider master or ground lease opportunities. Our primary structuring goal is to appropriately align our interests with those of our joint development partners.We will typically target the use of 75% debt leverage in achieving our desired investment returns.





Real Estate Services
Shop Your Way™


Property Sales and Leasing
TownCenter Partners LLC offers properties that are suitable for all kinds of business and commercial purposes. With a special emphasis on shopping centers, our sales and leasing team offers the best in experience and know-how. We can assist the sale or leasing of your property with a variety of important services:
                            • Full service brokerage 
                            • Property assessment and analysis 
                            • Strategic assessment of individual needs 
                            • Marketing strategies and implementation 
                            • Negotiations & Joint Ventures & Real Estate Equity Financing 
                            • Contract interpretation 
                            • Service Nationwide and Overseas 
                          • In-depth knowledge of Virginia, DC, and Maryland.


Buyer/Tenant Representation
Call TownCenter Partners LLC and we will discuss in detail the process by which we can help you identify your new facility and negotiate the optimum terms of a lease or purchase. We will help you assess your needs, conduct the search for your facility, and negotiate the rock bottom price and at the same time advise you as to how to structure the deal for future growth. 
                            • Needs Assessment 
                            • Site Selection and Comparative Analysis 
                            • Lease vs. Purchase Analysis 


Property Management
Our successful combination of marketing, research and specialization, together with each associate's knowledge of the market and client needs, is the reason so many owners and investors choose TownCenter Partners LLC to handle their commercial real estate transactions. A well-balanced effort consisting of accounting, reporting, property management and tenant retention includes: 
                            • Lease Administration 
                            • Operating and Capital Budgeting 
                            • Vendor Administration 
                            • Financial Reporting 
                            • Maintenance Bidding and Supervision 
                            • Construction Management 
                            • Tax Appeal Support 


Other Services and Listings
